HEADWORD: Asarabacca
<hw>As`a*ra*bac"ca</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>asarum</ets> + <ets>bacca</ets> a berry. See
<er>Asarone</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>An acrid herbaceous
plant (<spn>Asarum Europ⟦ae⟧um</spn>), the leaves and roots of which are
emetic and cathartic. It is principally used in cephalic
snuffs.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

